Biology
\f1\b0  is the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Science"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 scientific}} study of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Life"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 life}}.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super [1][2][3]
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub  It is a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Natural_science"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 natural science}} with a broad scope but has several unifying themes that tie it together as a single, coherent field.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super [1][2][3]
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub  For instance, all {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Organism"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 organisms}} are made up of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_(biology)"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 cells}} that process hereditary information encoded in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 genes}}, which can be transmitted to future generations. Another major theme is {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Evolution"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 evolution}}, which explains the unity and diversity of life.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super [1][2][3]
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub  {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metabolism"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Energy processing}} is also important to life as it allows organisms to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animal_locomotion"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 move}}, grow, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reproduce"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 reproduce}}.
\fs22\fsmilli11200 \cf4 \super [1][2][3]
\fs28 \cf2 \nosupersub  Finally, all organisms are able to regulate their own {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internal_environment"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 internal environments}}.}